cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Zikra in your work or research, please cite it using this metadata."
type: software
title: "Zikra — Persistent Memory for AI Coding Agents"
abstract: "Zikra is a self-hosted, MCP-native persistent memory server for AI coding agents. It provides a shared memory pool that Claude Code, Cursor, Gemini CLI, and other AI tools can read and write across sessions and machines. Built on PostgreSQL + pgvector + n8n."
authors:
  - name: "Zikra Contributors"
version: "1.0.1"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/getzikra/zikra"
url: "https://zikra.dev"
keywords:
  - claude-code
  - mcp
  - mcp-server
  - persistent-memory
  - ai-agents
  - n8n
  - postgresql
  - pgvector
  - self-hosted
  - llm-memory
